.SH NAME
i915_gem_object_read_from_page \- read data from the page of a GEM object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i915_gem_object_read_from_page
.BI "(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj "  ","
.BI "u64 offset "  ","
.BI "void *dst "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "obj" 12
GEM object to read from
.IP "offset" 12
offset within the object
.IP "dst" 12
buffer to store the read data
.IP "size" 12
size to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads data from \fIobj\fP at the specified offset. The requested region to read
from can't cross a page boundary. The caller must ensure that \fIobj\fP pages
are pinned and that \fIobj\fP is synced wrt. any related writes.

Returns 0 on success or -ENODEV if the type of \fIobj\fP's backing store is
unsupported.
